session-end` fires on process exit. If the session-end handler also saves a checkpoint when there are unsaved changes, then this PR would help.\\n\\nBut even if `session-end` does save a checkpoint, we still have the problem that `turn-end` is needed for the normal flow. Let me think about this differently.\\n\\nFor `opencode run`, the flow would be:\\n1. Process starts → `session.created` → plugin calls `session-start` hook ✓\\n2. User message → `message.part.updated` → plugin calls `turn-start` hook ✓\\n3. Agent does work (creates files, etc.)\\n4. Agent finishes → `session.idle` event doesn't fire in run mode\\n5. Process exits → `session.deleted` event doesn't fire in run mode\\n6. With PR #462: Watcher detects stdin close → calls `session-end` hook\\n\\nThe real issue is whether the `session-end` hook in the Entire CLI actually triggers a checkpoint save when there are unsaved changes, or if that's something I need to verify.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1178,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":145193,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1178},\"output_tokens\":8,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYR53axrRg9jtJ8vQLwcx\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"b9d1b305-54af-4c42-8606-767b025d027a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-23T13:21:55.068Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b9d1b305-54af-4c42-8606-767b025d027a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"905f477d-f712-4d89-9e62-a052775cec44\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/opencode-refactor\",\"slug\":\"polymorphic-wandering-teapot\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_017N4vcSDG7aB8j9kHu4Bvk5\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This PR adds a cleanup watcher that spawns a child