ion:\\n\\n**The parent Bun process will NOT exit until all child processes have exited.** By default:\\n- `Bun.spawnSync` is a blocking API that waits for the spawned process to complete\\n- The parent process will **wait** for all spawned children to finish naturally\\n- To allow a child to survive parent exit, you would need to call `proc.unref()` on the subprocess instance to detach it\\n\\nThis means if you spawn a process with `Bun.spawnSync` without calling `unref()`, the parent will block waiting for that child to complete before the parent can exit.\\n\\n## Key Implication\\n\\nIf OpenCode's `run` command uses `Bun.spawnSync` to spawn a subprocess (like a git hook process), the spawned process **will not survive** if the parent OpenCode process exits — the parent will wait for the child to complete first.\\n\\nSources:\\n- [Bun Spawn Documentation](https://bun.com/docs/runtime/child-process)\\n- [Bun.spawnSync API Reference](https://bun.com/reference/bun/spawnSync)\\n- [OpenCode Run Command Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/cli/)\\n- [OpenCode GitHub Repository](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode)\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a23b199 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 31349\\ntool_uses: 11\\nduration_ms: 1503963</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"8cd146ce-d49f-49c2-b96e-23d52415ac9b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-23T13:57:22.670Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"Search the OpenCode source code to understand how `opencode run` exits after detecting session.status idle. I need to know:\\n1. Does it call `process.exit()` immediately?\\n2. Does it await anything before exiting?\\n3. Is there a cleanup phase?\\n\\nLook in the OpenCode npm packages or GitHub source. The key file would be `packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/run.ts` or similar paths. Search for how the event loop breaks and what happens after.\\n\\nAlso search the Bun documentation to confirm that `Bun.spawnSync` works correctly - specifically whether the spawned process survives if the parent Node/Bun process is exiting.\",\"agentId\":\"a23b199\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Based on my research, here's what I found about OpenCode's exit behavior and Bun.spawnSync:\\n\\n## OpenCode Run Command Exit Behavior\\n\\n### 1. **Does it call `process.exit()` immediately?**\\n\\nNo, not in normal operation. The OpenCode `run.ts` command uses a **break statement** to exit the event loop gracefully:\\n\\n```typescript\\nif (\\n  event.type === \\\"session.status\\\" &&\\n  event.properties.sessionID === sessionID &&\\n  event.properties.status.type === \\\"idle\\\"\\n) {\\n  break  // Exits the async loop when session becomes idle\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe command detects when `session.status` becomes `\\\"idle\\\"` and simply breaks out of the event listening loop, allowing the handler to complete naturally.\\n\\n### 2. **Does it await anything before exiting?**\\n\\nYes, the implementation is event-driven and async:\\n- It listens to `session.status` events from the SDK event stream\\n- It awaits these events until the idle status is detected\\n- The break statement exits the listening loop gracefully\\n- The handler then completes normally without explicit cleanup\\n\\n### 3. **Is there a cleanup phase?**\\n\\nThe code only calls `process.exit(1)` in **error scenarios**:\\n- Uncaught exceptions in the event loop: `console.error(e); process.exit(1)`\\n- Validation failures (missing messages, invalid flags, file access issues)\\n\\nNormal completion is graceful without forced exit.\\n\\n## Bun.spawnSync Child Process Behavior\\n\\nAccording to Bun documentation:\\n\\n**The parent Bun process will NOT exit until all child processes have exited.** By default:\\n- `Bun.spawnSync` is a blocking API that waits for the spawned process to complete\\n- The parent process will **wait** for all spawned children to finish naturally\\n- To allow a child to survive parent exit, you would need to call `proc.unref()` on the subprocess instance to detach it\\n\\nThis means if you spawn a process with `Bun.spawnSync` without calling `unref()`, the parent will block waiting for that child to complete before the parent can exit.\\n\\n## Key Implication\\n\\nIf OpenCode's `run` command uses `Bun.spawnSync` to spawn a subprocess (like a git hook process), the spawned process **will not survive** if the parent OpenCode process exits — the parent will wait for the child to complete first.\\n\\nSources:\\n- [Bun Spawn Documentation](https://bun.com/docs/runtime/child-process)\\n- [Bun.spawnSync API Reference](https://bun.com/reference/bun/spawnSync)\\n- [OpenCode Run Command Documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/cli/)\\n- [OpenCode GitHub Repository](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode)\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":1503963,\"totalTokens\":31349,\"totalToolUseCount\":11,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":5,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":616,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":30061,\"output_tokens\":667,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":616,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"8e3f79f3-0869-4b01-820c-d17cc7283de0\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8cd146ce-d49f-49c2-b96e-23d52415ac9b\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli_experiments\",\"sessionId\":\"905f477d-f712-4d89-9e62-a052775cec44\",\"version\":\"2.1.47\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/opencode-refactor\",\"slug\":\"polymorphic-wandering-teapot\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Duiu1swvwKRSz1NrYoem5K\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nGood news from the research: OpenCode's `run` command exits **gracefully** (via `break` from the event loop), not via `process.exit()`. And `Bun.spawnSync` **blocks the parent pro